<body>

<div class="container">

    <h1>How Does Pharma Stock Work?</h1>
    <div class="subtitle">
        A step-by-step overview of the system workflow
    </div>

    <div class="step">
        <h2>Step 1: User Signup & Login</h2>
        <p>
            The pharmacy owner creates an account and logs in securely. Each user
            gets a private workspace where their inventory and sales data are
            isolated from others.
        </p>

        <img src="/assets/signup.png" alt="Login Page" class="screenshot">
        <div class="caption">Signup Interface</div>
        <img src="/assets/login.png" alt="Login Page" class="screenshot">
        <div class="caption">Login Interface</div>

    </div>

    <div class="step">
    <h2>Step 2: Profile & Account Management</h2>
    <p>
        Pharma Stock provides a dedicated profile section where users can manage
        their account-related information and ensure secure access to the system.
        This section helps users maintain updated details and control their session.
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li><strong>View Profile:</strong> Users can view their registered account and shop details.</li>
        <li><strong>Update Profile:</strong> Basic information such as name or contact details can be updated to keep records accurate.</li>
        <li><strong>Account Security:</strong> Profile access is restricted to the logged-in user only.</li>
        <li><strong>Logout:</strong> Users can securely log out to terminate their session, especially important on shared devices.</li>
    </ul>

        <img src="/assets/profile.png" alt="Login Page" class="screenshot">
        <div class="caption">View Profile</div>
        <img src="/assets/profile-update.png" alt="Login Page" class="screenshot">
        <div class="caption">Update Your Profile</div>
        <img src="/assets/logout.png" alt="Login Page" class="screenshot">
        <div class="caption">logout</div>

    <div class="note">
        Keeping profile information updated and logging out after use helps ensure
        data security and prevents unauthorized access.
    </div>
</div>


    <div class="step">
        <h2>Step 3: Add Medicines to Inventory</h2>
        <p>
            Medicines are added with essential details such as batch number,
            expiry date, quantity, and rack location. This batch-level entry
            ensures accurate tracking and compliance.
        </p>

        <img src="/assets/add.png" alt="Login Page" class="screenshot">
        <div class="caption">Add Medicines to Inventory</div>

    </div>


    <div class="step">
        <h2>Step 4: Sell Medicines (FEFO Logic)</h2>
        <p>
            During billing, the system follows the FEFO (First Expired, First Out)
            principle, ensuring that medicines nearing expiry are sold first,
            reducing wastage and loss.
        </p>

        <img src="/assets/billing.png" alt="Login Page" class="screenshot">
        <div class="caption">Generating Receipt</div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
        <h2>Step 5: Automatic Stock Update</h2>
        <p>
            Once a sale is completed, the system automatically deducts the sold
            quantity from the correct batch and updates stock levels in real time.
        </p>

        <img src="/assets/inventory.png" alt="Login Page" class="screenshot">
        <div class="caption">Inventory</div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
        <h2>Step 6: Sales History & Monitoring</h2>
        <p>
            All transactions are recorded and can be reviewed anytime. This helps
            shop owners analyze sales trends, track customers, and manage inventory
            efficiently.
        </p>

        <img src="/assets/customer-sale.png" alt="Login Page" class="screenshot">
        <div class="caption">Sales History</div>
    </div>

